definition.value: A branched amino octasaccharide consisting of a beta-D-GlcNAc residue at the reducing end with a beta-D-GlcNAc-(1->2)-alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-[beta-D-Xyl-(1->2)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc moiety attached via a beta-(1->4)-linkage and an alpha-L-Fuc residue attached via an alpha-(1->6)-linkage.
A D-gulofuranose that has beta configuration at the anomeric centre.
A linear amino tetrasaccharide comprising N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl, beta-D-galactosyl, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl and D-mannose residues linked sequentially (2->6), (1->4) and (1->2).
A divalent inorganic anion obtained by removal of both protons from hydrogen sulfide.

The amino hexasaccharide derivative alpha-D-Manp-(1->2)-alpha-D-Manp-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Manp-(1->6)]-beta-D-Manp-(1->4)-beta-GlcpNAc-(1->4)-D-GlcpNAc in which the anomeric configuration of the reducing-end GlcNAc residue is beta.
A D-lyxofuranose that has beta- configuration at the anomeric centre.
